Lisa was born in 1985 in a small town in the San Francisco Bay Area called San Lorenzo, California. There she enjoyed a happy childhood with her family.
<br>
<br>
While in college Lisa became interested in studying the [Spanish] language. She studied abroad at the [Centro de Lenguas Modernas] in Granada, Spain. In 2011 Lisa graduated from [California State University, East Bay] with a degree in English Language and Literature and a minor in Spanish. 
<br>
<br>
After graduating college, in 2012, Lisa returned to Spain to work as an [Auxiliar de Conversacion], funded by a grant from the Spanish government.
<br>
<br>
In 2015 Lisa return to the Bay Area from Spain and began studying web development and design. She completed a full stack web development bootcamp at [General Assembly]. 
<br>
<br>
In 2016 she completed a remote immersive course in UI/UX design at [DesignLab].
From 2016-17 she worked at [Dell EMC] as a web application designer and developer 
 In 2018 she, briefly, worked at [eBay] as a design engineer. She loves building apps, such as this [wiki]. Please hire her.